[[乔·拜登|乔·拜登]]的'''2020年总统竞选'''始于2019年4月25日，当时他发布了一段视频，宣布参加2020年[[民主党_(美国)|民主黨]]总统初选。拜登在2009年至2017年间担任[[美国副总统|副總統]]，并曾是[[特拉华州|特拉华州]]的前[[美国参议院|參議員]]。在拒绝成为[[2016年美國總統選舉|2016年大选]]的[[美国总统|總統]]候选人之后，拜登一直被广泛认为是2020年大选的潜在總統候选人。

拜登一般被称为{{link-en|温和派|Moderate}}，尽管最近他称自己为进步派。他的立场包括将[[罗诉韦德案|罗诉韦德案]]纳入法令、医疗保险的公共选择、娱乐性大麻的[[除罪化|除罪化]]、通过{{link-en|平等法|Equality Act (United States)}}、免费社区大学以及一项包含绿色新政框架的1.7万亿美元气候计划。他支持监管，而不是完全禁止[[水力压裂|水力压裂]]。

==初選==
作为前副总统，拜登以极高的知名度参选。从他的竞选宣言到选举开始，他一直是民主党最具领先地位的候选人。在2019年，他在全国大多数民调中领先，但无论是在爱荷华州还是在新罕布什尔州的初选中，他都没有成为前三名候选人之一。2020年2月29日，他在2020年南卡罗来纳州民主党初选中以压倒性优势获胜，为他的竞选注入了活力。2020年3月，他的10位前竞争对手背书他，使此类支持总数达到12次。拜登在2020年的超级星期二赢得了足够的代表，领先参议员[[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼·桑德斯]]。4月8日，桑德斯暂停竞选后，拜登成为预定民主党总统候选人。

2020年6月，拜登达到了提名所需的代表人数。2020年6月29日，[[拉斯穆森报导|拉斯穆森报导]]發表的一項[[民意調查|民意調查]]宣稱有38%的有意投票選民相信拜登患有某種形式的[[失智症|失智症]]，48%選民表示不同意，14%選民表示不確定，有20%的民主黨選民、66%的[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]選民和30%的兩黨以外選民相信拜登有失智症。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rasmussenreports.com/public_content/politics/elections/election_2020/38_of_voters_think_biden_has_dementia |title=38% of Voters Think Biden Has Dementia |website=Rasmussen Reports |date=2020-06-29 |access-date=2021-03-02 |archive-date=2021-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203053440/https://www.rasmussenreports.com/public_content/politics/elections/election_2020/38_of_voters_think_biden_has_dementia |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2020年7月3日，拜登在網路直播中疑似誤說「我是喬·拜登的丈夫」。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://sputniknews.com/us/202007041079794017-Joe-Biden-Biden-husband/ |script-title=en:Joe Biden Calls Himself ‘Joe Biden’s Husband’ in Verbal Slip-Up |website=sputniknews.com |date=2020-07-04 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2021-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627073643/https://sputniknews.com/us/202007041079794017-Joe-Biden-Biden-husband/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>7月20日，拜登說他希望美國的學校可以教授更多關於[[伊斯兰教|伊斯兰信仰]]的內容。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-muslim-voters-summit-taught-schools-islamic-faith |script-title=en:Biden, at Muslim voters summit, says ‘I wish we taught more in our schools about the Islamic faith’ |publisher=Fox News |date=2020-07-20 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2022-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127035316/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-muslim-voters-summit-taught-schools-islamic-faith |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2020年8月5日，拜登在被問到是否有接受認知測試時回答說沒有，並且反問為何他要接受測試。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-snaps-at-question-on-cognitive-test-likens-it-to-asking-reporter-if-hes-a-junkie |script-title=en:Biden snaps at question on cognitive test, likens it to asking reporter if he’s ‘a junkie’ |publisher=Fox News |date=2020-08-05 |accessdate=2021-03-02 |archive-date=2021-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227043953/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-snaps-at-question-on-cognitive-test-likens-it-to-asking-reporter-if-hes-a-junkie |dead-url=no }}</ref>8月10日，拉斯穆森报导發表的另一項民調宣稱有59%有意投票選民認為拜登如果在11月當選總統的話，他頗可能在4年任期內被副總統接替。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rasmussenreports.com/public_content/politics/elections/election_2020/59_think_biden_unlikely_to_finish_a_four_year_term_in_white_house |title=59% Think Biden Unlikely to Finish A Four-Year Term in White House |publisher=Rasmussen Reports |date=2020-08-10 |access-date=2021-03-02 |archive-date=2021-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131135429/https://www.rasmussenreports.com/public_content/politics/elections/election_2020/59_think_biden_unlikely_to_finish_a_four_year_term_in_white_house |dead-url=no }}</ref>8月11日，拜登宣布加州参议员[[賀錦麗|賀錦麗]]将成为他的副总统竞选伙伴。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/kamala-harris-biden-running-mate-what-to-know |title=Kamala Harris chosen as Biden’s running mate: What to know |publisher=Fox News |date=2020-08-11 |accessdate=2021-03-02 |archive-date=2020-08-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200811223324/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/kamala-harris-biden-running-mate-what-to-know |dead-url=no }}</ref>8月18日和19日，拜登和賀錦麗在2020年民主党全国代表大会上获得正式提名，这使賀錦麗成为第一位在主要政党票上被提名为副总统的[[亚裔美国人|亚裔美国人]]和第一位女性[[非裔美国人|非裔美国人]]。<ref name="APResonate">{{Cite news |date=August 12, 2020 |title=Kamala Harris' selection as VP resonates with Black women |agency=Associated Press |url=https://apnews.com/46ef207f32a089b2b54ed35d57c9413f |quote=making her the first Black woman on a major party's presidential ticket... It also marks the first time a person of Asian descent is on the presidential ticket. |accessdate=2020-10-09 |archive-date=2020-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200812075528/https://apnews.com/46ef207f32a089b2b54ed35d57c9413f |dead-url=no }}</ref>拜登在大會網路直播上再次誤說「我是喬·拜登的丈夫」。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/dnc-2020-bill-clinton-will-excoriate-trump-chaos-storm-center-n1237190 |title=Bill Clinton says at DNC Trump ignored COVID-19 while 'zapping people on social media' |website=nbcnews.com |date=2020-08-19 |quote="I'm Joe Biden's husband," he said. |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2021-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223033139/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/dnc-2020-bill-clinton-will-excoriate-trump-chaos-storm-center-n1237190 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2020年进行的全国民意調查总体上显示拜登較特朗普獲得更高支持率。

==獲得民主黨提名後==
上屆敗選的[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]在8月25日發佈的受訪片段表示「不論任何情況」拜登都不應承認敗選，因為屆時將需要更長時間才知道最終結果，她相信民主黨只要寸步不讓，以及有跟對手同樣的專注和努力，拜登就會勝選。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/hillary-clinton-says-biden-should-not-concede-2020-election-under-n1238156 |title=Hillary Clinton says Biden should not concede the election 'under any circumstances' |website=nbcnews.com |date=2020-08-26 |quote=Joe Biden should not concede under any circumstances, because I think this is going to drag out, and eventually I do believe he will win if we don't give an inch, and if we are as focused and relentless as the other side is |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2022-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220103165739/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/hillary-clinton-says-biden-should-not-concede-2020-election-under-n1238156 |dead-url=no }}</ref>8月27日，民主黨籍的眾議院議長[[南希·佩洛西|南希·佩洛西]]在記者會表示鑒於特朗普在2016年對希拉里·克林頓的[[纏擾|纏擾]]，拜登不應與特朗普進行任何（電視）辯論。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.speaker.gov/newsroom/82720-1 |title=Transcript of Pelosi Weekly Press Conference Today |website=speaker.gov |date=2020-08-27 |quote=Since you asked about that, I, myself – just don't tell anybody I told you this, especially don't tell Joe Biden.  I don't think that there should be any debates. |access-date=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2021-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223033126/https://www.speaker.gov/newsroom/82720-1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2020年9月3日，拜登在[[威斯康星州|威斯康星州]][[基诺沙_(威斯康辛州)|基诺沙市]]拜票时，质疑为什么不在历史课上教历史，并宣稱[[電燈泡|電燈泡]]是由一位黑人發明，「不是一位名叫[[愛迪生|愛迪生]]的白人男人」，引起争议。他还提到[[塔尔萨大屠杀|1921年塔尔萨种族大屠杀]]和俄克拉荷马州黑色华尔街的破坏，称这是在学校没有教授的<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/04/us/biden-lightbulb-black-man-trnd/index.html |title=No, a Black man didn't invent the light bulb. But Lewis Howard Latimer made it better |publisher=CNN |date=2020-09-04 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2021-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223033141/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/04/us/biden-lightbulb-black-man-trnd/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-claims-black-man-invented-light-bulb-during-campaign-event |title=Biden claims Black man invented light bulb during campaign event |publisher=Fox News |date=2020-09-04 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2021-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223033139/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-claims-black-man-invented-light-bulb-during-campaign-event |dead-url=no }}</ref>。拜登在访问基诺沙市期间也发表了另一番尴尬的评论。他在演讲时谈到税收不平等问题，但他停止详细说明自己的税收政策，说如果他再继续说下去，「他们会开枪打死我」<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=en:Biden makes awkward ‘they’ll shoot me’ quip during Kenosha appearance|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-awkward-theyll-shoot-me-quip-kenosha|accessdate=2020-09-05|date=2020-09-03|last=Schultz|first=Marisa|work=Fox News|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223033132/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-awkward-theyll-shoot-me-quip-kenosha|dead-url=no}}</ref>。9月9日，拜登在[[密歇根州|密歇根州]]演說時誤稱有118,984名美軍人員感染[[2019冠狀病毒病|2019冠狀病毒病]]，6,114名美軍人員死亡（根據國防部數字，截至9月9日有40,026名軍人受感染，7名軍人死亡）<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/2009/09/cnr.11.html |title=Transcripts |publisher=CNN |date=2020-09-09 |quote=U.S. COVID-infected military -- excuse me, U.S. COVID infected in America, 6,344,700. U.S. COVID deaths, 189,506. Military COVID infected, 118,984. Military COVID deaths, 6,114. |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2020-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201016180905/http://edition.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/2009/09/cnr.11.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/09/politics/joe-biden-us-troop-covid-deaths-fact-check/index.html |title=Fact check: Biden way overstates the number of military deaths and cases from Covid |publisher=CNN |date=2020-09-09 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2021-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223033124/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/09/politics/joe-biden-us-troop-covid-deaths-fact-check/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。9月20日，拜登在演說時誤稱如果讓特朗普用自己的一套處理[[2019冠狀病毒病|2019冠狀病毒病]]疫情，大概在他該次演說完結之時，「估計已有2億人死亡」<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-says-200-million-die-from-covid |title=Biden says 200 million people have died from coronavirus as campaign gaffes continue |publisher=Fox News |date=2020-09-20 |quote="If Donald Trump has his way, the complications from COVID-19, which are well beyond what they should be -- it's estimated that 200 million people have died -- probably by the time I finish this talk," he said during a campaign speech. |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2021-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223033125/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-says-200-million-die-from-covid |dead-url=no }}</ref>。9月26日，拜登在美國市長會議發言時誤稱自己在180年前成為參議員。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://sputniknews.com/us/202009261080583292-well-preserved-joe-biden-suggests-he-was-elected-to-senate-180-years-ago---video/ |title=Well-Preserved? Joe Biden Suggests He Was Elected to Senate '180 Years Ago' - Video |website=sputniknews.com |date=2020-09-26 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2020-12-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201230011800/https://sputniknews.com/us/202009261080583292-well-preserved-joe-biden-suggests-he-was-elected-to-senate-180-years-ago---video/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

预定的三场总统辩论中的第一场于9月29日举行。特朗普不停地侮辱和打断拜登，经常打断主持人[[克里斯·华莱士|克里斯·华莱士]]问问题。这一事件被广泛被批评为总统选举政治的低谷。

10月8日，拜登在被問到如果他當選以及民主黨重掌參議院，他會否支持[[1937年司法程序改革法案|擴充最高法院大法官人數]]時答道「在選舉後的第一日你將會知道我對於填充法院的立場」，未有表明支持或否，次日他又被記者提問類似問題，在記者問他「選民不是有權知道嗎」時，拜登答他們沒有權（知道）。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-voters-deserve-packing-supreme-court |title=Biden says voters don't deserve to know his stance on packing Supreme Court |publisher=Fox News |date=2020-10-10 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2022-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324062426/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-voters-deserve-packing-supreme-court |dead-url=no }}</ref>

